{"pdf_page": 356, "w": 1434, "h": 2330, "dpi": 300, "blocks": [{"order": 0, "label": "SectionHeader", "conf": 0.962, "html": "<h3>PLATE No. 3.</h3>", "bbox": [570.7320000000001, 253.97, 867.5699999999999, 309.89000000000004]}, {"order": 1, "label": "Text", "conf": 0.962, "html": "<p><b>ANANT—The Endless.</b></p>", "bbox": [136.23, 363.48, 542.052, 412.40999999999997]}, {"order": 2, "label": "Text", "conf": 0.962, "html": "<p>It is the accepted picture of (1) Vishnu, who is supposed to be the Sun, (2) of Lakshmi, the Earth, and of (3) Brahma, the refraction of the Sun. <i>See</i> page xl.</p>", "bbox": [212.232, 463.67, 1307.808, 624.44]}]}